        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-03-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-03-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="101" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d101">
                <head>No. 101.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Hall</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-03-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 23, 1888</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 560.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have pleasure in transmitting for your
                    information a copy of a note from the minister of Italy<note n="†" xml:id="d101fn1">For inclosure see Doc. No. 722, <hi rend="italic">post</hi>, p. 1050, under “Italian correspondence.”</note> here, dated the
                    18th instant, conveying <pb facs="0268" n="134" xml:id="pg_134"/> an expression
                    of his Government’s thanks for your efforts in bringing to an equitable
                    adjustment the claim of the Italian Sagrini against Salvador.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">T. F. Bayard.</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
